level.heading:
ALTERNATIVE SANCTIONS FOR ICFSIID-NON-IMMEDIATE JEOPARDY (§ 29-4111)
    In accordance with Section 1902(i)(1)(B) of the Social Security Act, the District of Columbia may impose alternative sanctions against an ICF/IID when that facility fails to meet the CoPs, but the violation does not place beneficiary health or safety
      in immediate jeopardy.
    In lieu of terminating the provider agreement, DHCF may impose one (1) or more alternative sanctions against an ICF/IID as set forth below:
    Denial of payment, as described in § 4112;
    Directed Plan of Correction (DPoC), as described in § 4113;
    Directed In-Service Training (DIST), as described in § 4114; or
    State Monitoring, as described in § 4115.
    Seriousness of the violation(s);
    Number and nature of the violation(s);
    Potential for immediate and serious threat(s) to ICF/IID residents;
    Potential for serious harm to ICF/IID residents;
    Any history of prior violation(s) and/or sanction(s);
    Actions or recommendations of DDS, developmental disability advocacy groups, or health care entities;
    Mitigating circumstances; and
    Other relevant factors.
